The paper deals with metadata reconciliation and curation for Open Governmental Data Portals (ODPs), which involves organizing and linking datasets using tags. This topic is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL) techniques that can be used for semantic tagging and linking. Additionally, the paper discusses issues related to data quality and governance (cs.CY), which are important considerations for ODPs.
